item.title: Power BI Engineer Required for Redevelopment/ Enhancement of Reports - Upwork
item.description:
*Please read carefully till the end before applying*

- This is a full time contractual opportunity for at least 4 months

- This opportunity is on-site for our client based in Thailand. So, this project will require you to stay in Thailand for at least 2 months out of the 4 month project. All travel and stay expenses will be covered.

- We will give preference to candidates based in India, however, we are willing to consider the right candidates from other countries as well.

- The final Interview may happen on a zoom/google meet call outside of upwork. The contract will then be made on upwork.

- English Communication skills are important.

We are looking for 2 X Power BI developers for -

1. Re-development/Enhancement of Power BI Reports
2. Collaborate with the client IT team to understand and gather business requirements.
3. Ensure all business requirements are well-documented and clearly understood before implementation.
4. Create and maintain comprehensive documentation for all developed and enhanced Power BI reports.
5. Document the data sources, data models, transformations, and any custom calculations used in the reports.

Qualifications -

- Proven experience as a Power BI Developer or in a similar role.
- Proficiency in Power BI, including Power Query, DAX, and Power BI Service.
- Strong understanding of data warehousing concepts, data modeling, and ETL processes.
- Experience with SQL and other database query languages.
- Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.
- Strong communication and interpersonal skills.
- Ability to work independently and as part of a team.

item.title: Data Analyst for Comprehensive Marketing and Performance Dashboard Development - Upwork
item.description:
We are a group of eye care clinics seeking an experienced data analyst to design and develop a comprehensive dashboard. This dashboard will consolidate and visualise key performance metrics from various marketing and performance tracking platforms. Currently, we use Google Analytics 4 (GA4), Google Ads, Meta Ads, TikTok, Funnel, and Zapier, with data being reported in Google Sheets. However, this solution is limited, and we require a more robust and sophisticated tool to effectively track and compare metrics such as website traffic, traffic sources, unique bookings, phone calls, and more, on a daily and weekly basis.

This initial project will focus on one clinic, and based on its success, we plan to replicate the dashboard across our other clinics. We are open to adopting new tools or software to achieve our objectives. Furthermore, if the project is successful, we are open to offering a part-time or full-time position.

**Responsibilities:**
- Integrate data from GA4, Google Ads, Meta Ads, TikTok, Funnel, and Zapier into a cohesive and comprehensive dashboard.
- Design and develop an intuitive, user-friendly dashboard that effectively visualises key performance metrics.
- Enable the dashboard to facilitate data comparison on a daily and weekly basis.
- Automate data updates and report generation processes.
- Potentially replicate the dashboard for additional clinics based on the initial project's success.

**Requirements:**
- Proven experience as a data analyst or in a similar role.
- Strong proficiency with GA4, GTM and other marketing platforms.
- Expertise in data visualisation tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or similar.
- Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.
- Ability to work independently and meet project deadlines.
- Strong communication skills to explain technical details to non-technical team members.

**Preferred Qualifications:**
- Experience with SQL and data manipulation.
- Familiarity with Google Data Studio.
- Knowledge of web analytics and digital marketing.

**Application Process:**
Please provide:
- A brief introduction about yourself and your relevant experience.
- Examples of previous dashboards you have created.
- Your proposed approach to this project.
- Estimated timeline and cost.

We look forward to your applications and to potentially welcoming you to our team!


Budget: $500
Posted On: July 26, 2024 10:22 UTC
Category: Data Analytics
Skills:Data Analysis, Microsoft Excel, Business Intelligence, Google Analytics
Skills: Data Analysis, Microsoft Excel, Business Intelligence, Google Analytics
Country: Germany

  - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a PowerBI specialist to create a comprehensive dashboard and manage table/data relationships in PowerBI. The dashboard should enable us to gain valuable insights and make data-driven decisions.

Job Scope:
- Design and develop a user-friendly and visually appealing dashboard with relevant charts and metrics.
- Review and improve the database table relationships.
- Advise on any missing data sources based on requirements.
- Build relational databases between different data sources, such as Xero between Jira.
- Ensure data accuracy and consistency between the sources and the PowerBI dashboard.
- Provide insights and recommendations based on the data visualization.
- Troubleshoot and resolve any issues related to data integration and visualization.

Requirements:
- Proven experience in PowerBI dashboard creation and data visualization.
- Experience with Xero and Jira software will be a plus.  
- Good analytical skills.
- Ability to review and improve data and table relationships.
- Ability to advise on missing data sources based on requirements.
- Ability to build relational databases between different data sources.
- Excellent communication skills to understand requirements and provide regular updates.

Examples:
- Profit and loss per team: Analyze financial performance by team.
- Company performance: Analyse time & task allocation per team
- Actual vs Forecasted data dashboard analysis  
- Historical performance
- around 50 charts / tables

item.title: PowerApp - Dashboard & Timeline - Upwork
item.description:
We need to create a PoC application made in PowerApps with custom UI for the shipping industry and with dummy data to showcase basic functionality of the app. We have 3 days/72 hours of time for which we need a custom budget.
We have a UI already made but need to be built on PowerApps (UI: https://bit.ly/3zS0pPC, Video with more info: https://we.tl/t-i4IBF6YZA7

The project scope:
1. Create a dashboard like in the video (with dummy data)
2. The vessel data is shown in various views - operator view (only access to one vessel), manager view (some vessels), operator view (all vessels)
3. When a vessel is chosen, show properties like video
4. Show timeline of vessel arrival based on different inputs
5. Create vessel timeline & fuel consumption based on speed

The point here is to make a PoC and show functionality rather than accuracy with real data. We need to show this is possible to create. If we can create this, we’ll have a much larger contract too to actually build it out.

item.title: Senior Power BI - Upwork
item.description:
Position Overview:
As a Senior Business Intelligence Technical Lead, you will play a crucial role in transforming raw data into actionable insights for our organization. Leveraging your extensive experience in BI development and analytics, leading team & you will collaborate with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and maintain robust BI solutions that drive informed decision-making.

Responsibilities:
1. Expert Knowledge of Power BI:
Proficiency in creating reports, dashboards, and interactive visualizations using Power BI.
Strong understanding of Power BI service and Power BI Desktop functionalities.

2.Data Modeling:
Expertise in designing and implementing data models that support robust reporting and analytics.
Knowledge of star schema, snowflake schema, and other data modeling techniques.

3.Power Query:
Advanced skills in data transformation and preparation using Power Query.
Experience in creating and managing data flows.

4.DAX (Data Analysis Expressions):
In-depth understanding of DAX for data manipulation and calculation within Power BI.
Ability to write complex DAX expressions for advanced analytics.


5.Data Visualization:
Strong ability to create meaningful and insightful visual representations of data.
Knowledge of best practices for visual design and user experience.

6.Data Flow:
Experience in managing and automating data flows from various data sources to Power BI.
Understanding of data integration and data quality management.

7.Custom Visual Development:
Skills in developing custom visuals for Power BI using tools such as TypeScript and D3.js.
Ability to extend the functionality of Power BI by creating tailored visualizations.


8.Strong Programming Skills in SQL:
Proficiency in writing complex SQL queries for data extraction, manipulation, and analysis.
Experience with different SQL-based database management systems.

9.Experience with ETL Tools (ADF, SSIS):

Practical experience using ETL tools such as Azure Data Factory (ADF) and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) for data extraction, transformation, and loading.
Knowledge of designing, developing, and maintaining ETL processes.


10.Excellent Communication and Presentation Skills:

Ability to effectively communicate technical information to non-technical stakeholders.
Strong presentation skills to share insights and findings with diverse audiences.
Experience in collaborating with cross-functional teams to gather requirements and deliver solutions.

Preferred Qualifications:

1.Certifications:
Relevant certifications in Power BI, SQL, or data warehousing can be an advantage.

2.Analytical Mindset:
Strong problem-solving skills and an analytical mindset to derive actionable insights from data.
3.Continuous Learning:

Commitment to staying updated with the latest trends and advancements in BI tools and technologies

Hourly Range: $15.00-$19.00

Category: Data Visualization
Skills:Microsoft Power BI, Business Intelligence, Microsoft Power BI Data Visualization, SQL, Data Analysis, Data Visualization, SQL Server Integration Services
Skills: Microsoft Power BI, Business Intelligence, Microsoft Power BI Data Visualization, SQL, Data Analysis, Data Visualization, SQL Server Integration Services
Country: United States

item.title: Upwork Lead Generation Specialist for Analytics Agency - Upwork
item.description:
Our web analytics agency is looking for Upwork lead generation assistance. We help our clients set up conversion tracking for Google Analytics 4, Google Ads, Meta Pixel, and other tools; and make custom reports and dashboards in Looker Studio and Power BI.

We need someone who's a kickstart, self-motivated, and consistent with this task.

You'd be responsible for the following:

– Documenting lead data via a simple Google Sheets document.
– Submitting customized proposals.
– Communicating with potential leads to book a call.
– Getting access to needed platforms from clients.
– Transferring tasks to the web analytics team
– You would be submitting somewhat customized proposals to our given criteria via Upwork.

It's important that you're fluent in English so you can create customized proposals.

Having a Google Analytics Individual Qualification certificate would be beneficial.

The first two sentences of the proposal you send for us MUST be original and not AI-generated or copy & paste. This is crucial for making a good first impression and showing genuine interest in the potential client.

The position starts at a base of 5 hours a week + 5% commission for a won contract.

The commission will be increased when you reach the total revenue amount:
– 7% after $5000
– 10% after $10000

Warm regards,
Denis

Hourly Range: $5.00-$10.00

item.title: Power BI and SQL required having 4+ years of experience  - Upwork
item.description:
Job Title: Experienced Power BI and SQL Specialist Needed

 
We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Power BI and SQL Specialist to join our team. The ideal candidate will have a minimum of 4 years of hands-on experience in developing, designing, and maintaining Power BI reports and dashboards, as well as strong expertise in SQL for data manipulation, extraction, and analysis.

Responsibilities:

Develop, design, and maintain interactive and visually appealing Power BI reports and dashboards.
Write and optimize complex SQL queries to extract and manipulate data from various databases.
Collaborate with stakeholders to gather requirements and ensure the delivery of accurate and meaningful insights.
Conduct data analysis to identify trends, patterns, and key metrics.
Ensure data quality and integrity in all reports and dashboards.
Perform data validation and troubleshooting to resolve issues and discrepancies.
Provide technical support and training to end-users on Power BI functionalities.
Continuously improve and optimize existing Power BI reports and SQL queries for better performance and user experience.
Requirements:

Minimum of 4 years of professional experience with Power BI and SQL.
Proficiency in writing complex SQL queries for data extraction, manipulation, and analysis.
Strong understanding of data visualization principles and best practices.
Experience in connecting to various data sources, including databases, spreadsheets, and cloud services.
Ability to create and maintain Power BI data models, DAX measures, and calculated columns.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail.
Excellent communication skills and the ability to work collaboratively with cross-functional teams.
Experience with data warehousing, ETL processes, and database management is a plus.
Power BI certification and/or SQL certification is a plus.
Preferred Qualifications:

Experience with other BI tools (e.g., Tableau, QlikView) is a plus.
Familiarity with programming languages such as Python or R for data analysis.
Knowledge of data governance and security best practices.
Application Process:

If you meet the above requirements and are passionate about leveraging data to drive business insights, we would love to hear from you. Please submit your resume, a cover letter detailing your relevant experience, and examples of your previous Power BI projects and SQL queries.

Budget: $2,300

item.title: Build demo dashboards in our style in Power BI for showcasing purposes - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a skilled Power BI Dashboard Developer to create a series of professional and visually appealing dashboards using dummy data. These dashboards will be used for showcasing purposes to potential clients. The successful candidate will be responsible for generating the data, creating the dashboards in our specified style, and ensuring they meet our requirements.

Key Responsibilities:
1. Data Generation: Generate realistic dummy data for various business functions.
2. Dashboard Creation: Develop Power BI dashboards based on the generated data.

3.Customization: Apply our provided theme and style to the dashboards.

Dashboard Topics: Create comprehensive dashboards for each of the following topics, structured into strategic, tactical/analytical, and operational pages (approximately 5 pages per dashboard):

1. Finance
Strategic KPI Page:
Revenue and Profit Trends
ROI
Gross Margin
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Expense Breakdown (by category, department)
Budget vs. Actual Analysis
Financial Ratios (current ratio, debt to equity)
Operational Pages:
Cash Flow Details (inflows and outflows)
Monthly/Quarterly Financial Statements
Transaction Details

2. Sales
Strategic KPI Page:
Total Sales
Sales Growth Rate
Market Share
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Sales by Product/Service
Sales Pipeline Analysis (leads, opportunities, conversion rates)
Regional Sales Performance
Operational Pages:
Detailed Sales Transactions
Sales Target vs. Actual Performance
Customer Segmentation and Sales Distribution

3. Marketing
Strategic KPI Page:
Campaign ROI
Customer Acquisition Cost
Lead Generation
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Campaign Performance Analysis
Market Segmentation and Demographics
Social Media Engagement Metrics
Operational Pages:
Detailed Campaign Spend and Outcomes
Conversion Rates by Channel
Detailed Customer Journey Analysis

4. Service
Strategic KPI Page:
Customer Satisfaction Score (CSAT)
Net Promoter Score (NPS)
Average Resolution Time
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Service Request Volume and Trends
Response and Resolution Time Analysis
Support Channel Performance (phone, email, chat)
Operational Pages:
Detailed Ticket Analysis
Customer Feedback and Ratings
Detailed Service Level Agreement (SLA) Compliance

5. HR
Strategic KPI Page:
Employee Turnover Rate
Employee Engagement Score
Diversity Metrics
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Performance Ratings and Trends
Training and Development Analysis
Headcount by Department and Location
Operational Pages:
Detailed Payroll Overview
Recruitment Funnel Metrics
Detailed Employee Satisfaction Survey Results

6. Projects
Strategic KPI Page:
Project Completion Rate
Budget Adherence
Resource Utilization
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Project Timeline and Milestone Analysis (Gantt charts)
Risk Assessment and Mitigation Plans
Resource Allocation and Load Analysis
Operational Pages:
Detailed Task and Activity Tracking
Budget vs. Actual Cost Analysis
Detailed Status Reports and Issue Logs

7. Supply Chain
Strategic KPI Page:
Inventory Turnover Rate
Supplier On-time Delivery Rate
Logistics Cost
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Inventory Levels and Trends
Supplier Performance Metrics (quality scores, lead times)
Demand Forecasting vs. Actual Sales
Operational Pages:
Detailed Procurement Metrics
Shipment and Delivery Tracking
Detailed Inventory Movements and Adjustments

8. CEO Management Dashboard
Strategic KPI Page:
Overview of Key Performance Indicators from all departments
Strategic Goal Progress
Financial Health Summary
Tactical/Analytical Pages:
Departmental Performance Summaries (Finance, Sales, Marketing, etc.)
Cross-departmental Trends and Analysis
Strategic Initiatives and Project Updates
Operational Pages:
Detailed Operational Metrics from each department
Compliance and Risk Management Insights
Detailed Analysis of Strategic Goal Metrics

Deliverables:
Excel File: A comprehensive Excel file containing the generated dummy data for each pbix-file.

Power BI Dashboards: A total of 8 fully functional Power BI dashboards, each dedicated to one of the topics listed above, adhering to our specified style, and structured with strategic, tactical/analytical, and operational pages.

item.title: Live Data Visualisation for a Database - Upwork
item.description:
We are working on an exciting project that analyzes data and derives various visualizations from it. The exact project details will be shared during a call.

We are looking for an expert developer to help us set up data collection through forms, maintain a database, and create the required interactive data visualizations. The visualizations need to be interactive with motion. This is a small workflow that needs to be implemented, and we are targeting a timeline of 2 weeks.

Our team of designers will work closely with you to implement the vision.

Brief Scope of Work:
1. User-Facing Interface:
    - Develop a form to collect data, hosted on a Squarespace website with custom form integration.
    - Ensure the form's responsiveness aligns with the rest of the website in terms of scaling fonts and grids.
    - Interactive Graphics: Implement interactive graphics on the webpage using WebGL (preferred but optional).
    - Live Data Plot: Create an independent page showcasing a live plot of the entire collected data with interactive 3D visualization and motion.
    - Mail Triggers: Implement email notifications upon submission of pledges.
2. Database and Processing:
    - Data Logging: Maintain a log of data submitted by users, including details about location, time, and revision history.
    - Data Analysis: Derive values based on set criteria for the data collected using the OpenAI API to an analysis. Ensure stable data taking into consideration the variability since we will be using AI and putting required measures in play for error handling.
3. Security and Compliance
    - Documentation: Document data encryption methods and compliance with GDPR and CCPA. Define measures taken for performance, scalability, reliability, and security.

Requirements:
- Experience with Squarespace and custom form integration.
- Strong knowledge of Python for data processing and visualization.
- Experience with OpenAI API for data analysis.
- Ability to create 3D visualizations with motion.
- Familiarity with data encryption, GDPR, and CCPA compliance.
- Proficiency in WebGL for interactive graphics (optional but preferred).

Additional Information:
- The project requires both 2D and 3D data visualizations.
- Successful collaboration on this project could lead to future opportunities.

Hourly Range: $15.00-$30.00

Category: Data Visualization
Skills:API Integration, Tableau, SQL, Matplotlib, JavaScript, Python, HTML, CSS, GoDaddy, GDPR
